<subSubSection id="E1974BE5FFD7044EE6ED8B40DC5D32FB" pageId="8" pageNumber="463" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="A932186EFFD7044EE6ED8B40DC5D32FB" blockId="8.[151,1437,259,538]" pageId="8" pageNumber="463">
<emphasis id="9BF9C47CFFD7044EE6ED8B40D930324F" bold="true" box="[199,314,331,357]" pageId="8" pageNumber="463">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Propodeum without wrinkles, with deep smooth anteromedian concavity. Fore wing vein 2m-cu strongly inclivous. Basal portion of first tarsomere (
<figureCitation id="31B604EBFFD7044EE4F78B64DB2532A3" box="[733,815,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1489,1513]" captionTargetBox="[162,1412,282,1456]" captionTargetId="figure-49@9.[162,1424,273,1466]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 25–30. Megastylus (Megastylus) yindianense Sheng &amp; Li, sp. nov. Holotype. Female. 25 Mesosoma, lateral view 26 Propodeum. 27 Front tibia and basal portion of tarsus, lateral view 28 Fore wing 29 Tergites 1–2, lateral view 30 Apical portion of metasoma, lateral view" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5848345" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5848345/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="463">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
) strongly curved concave, inner profile with dense fine setae, spur reach to middle of concavity. Tergite 1 mat, with dense indistinct punctures. Mesopleuron, mesosternum, hind coxa and femur and tibia except subbase and apex slightly black, reddish brown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
