<emphasis id="9BF9C47CFFD7044EE6ED8D2DD90D346A" bold="true" box="[199,263,1830,1856]" pageId="8" pageNumber="463">Head</emphasis>
. Face (
<figureCitation id="31B604EBFFD7044EE7708D2DD9A1346A" box="[346,427,1830,1856]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–24" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1723,1747]" captionTargetBox="[180,1420,564,1693]" captionTargetId="figure-143@8.[161,1427,561,1700]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 21–24. Megastylus (Megastylus) yindianense Sheng &amp; Li, sp. nov. Holotype. Female. 21 Habitus, lateral view 22 Head, anterior view 23 Head and pronotum, lateral view 24 Head and mesoscutum, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5848343" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5848343/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="463">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
) 1.4 × as wide as long, slightly convex, with sparse brown setae; almost parallel laterally, smooth, shiny; upper margin with small indistinct median tubercle. Clypeal sulcus distinct. Anterior tentorial pit relatively small, upper margin distinctly below a line connecting lower margins of eyes. Clypeus strongly convex, texture as face, 1.7 × as wide as long, median portion of apical margin weakly arched forwardly. Mandible with two sharp teeth. Malar space 1.4 × as long as basal width of mandible. Subocular sulcus distinctly exist. Gena and vertex (
<figureCitation id="31B604EBFFD7044EE6C48DD1D95F34DE" box="[238,341,2010,2036]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1768,1792]" captionTargetBox="[183,1419,631,1742]" captionTargetId="figure-176@2.[166,1420,631,1742]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Megastylus (Dicolus) mentouense Sheng &amp; Li, sp. nov. Holotype. Male. 1 Habitus, lateral view 2 Head, anterior view 3 Head, dorsal view 4 Head and pronotum, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5848333" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5848333/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="463">Figs 3, 4</figureCitation>
) shiny, posterior portion converging to occipital carina. Postocellar line 1.1 × as long as ocular- ocellar line. Antenna with 35–37 flagellomeres; flagellomeres with relatively longer setae. Ratio of length from first to fifth flagellomeres: 11.5:4.7:4.3:3.8:3.4. Occipital carina complete, joining hypostomal carina far above base of mandible.
</paragraph>
<caption id="FDF248E6FFD6044FE6BD8FDAD9E6351B" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5848345" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5848345" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5848345/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="464" startId="9.[151,264,1489,1513]" targetBox="[162,1412,282,1456]" targetPageId="9">
<paragraph id="A932186EFFD6044FE6BD8FDAD9E6351B" blockId="9.[151,1437,1489,1585]" pageId="9" pageNumber="464">
<emphasis id="9BF9C47CFFD6044FE6BD8FDAD94436C3" bold="true" box="[151,334,1489,1513]" pageId="9" pageNumber="464">FIGURES 25–30</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="6E8D63EDFFD6044FE7768FDADB5436C3" authority="Sheng &amp; Li" authorityName="Sheng &amp; Li" authorityYear="2022" box="[348,862,1489,1514]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Megastylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="464" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yindianense" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Megastylus">
<emphasis id="9BF9C47CFFD6044FE7768FDAD9C536C3" box="[348,463,1489,1513]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="464">Megastylus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="9BF9C47CFFD6044FE7CA8FDADA5936C3" box="[480,595,1489,1513]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="464">Megastylus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="9BF9C47CFFD6044FE4498FDADAD636C3" box="[611,732,1489,1513]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="464">yindianense</emphasis>
Sheng &amp; Li
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="9BF9C47CFFD6044FE5408FD9DBB136C0" bold="true" box="[874,955,1490,1514]" pageId="9" pageNumber="464">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="80CA7907FFD6044FE5408FD9DBB136C0" box="[874,955,1490,1514]" pageId="9" pageNumber="464" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
Holotype. Female. 
<emphasis id="9BF9C47CFFD6044FE2A28FDADCAB36C3" bold="true" box="[1160,1185,1489,1513]" pageId="9" pageNumber="464">25</emphasis>
Mesosoma, lateral view 
<emphasis id="9BF9C47CFFD6044FE6BD8FFED8BA3527" bold="true" box="[151,176,1525,1549]" pageId="9" pageNumber="464">26</emphasis>
Propodeum. 
<emphasis id="9BF9C47CFFD6044FE7168FFED95F3527" bold="true" box="[316,341,1525,1549]" pageId="9" pageNumber="464">27</emphasis>
Front tibia and basal portion of tarsus, lateral view 
<emphasis id="9BF9C47CFFD6044FE55F8FFEDB843527" bold="true" box="[885,910,1525,1549]" pageId="9" pageNumber="464">28</emphasis>
Fore wing 
<emphasis id="9BF9C47CFFD6044FE2228FFEDC2B3527" bold="true" box="[1032,1057,1525,1549]" pageId="9" pageNumber="464">29</emphasis>
Tergites 1–2, lateral view 
<emphasis id="9BF9C47CFFD6044FE3128FFEDD5B3527" bold="true" box="[1336,1361,1525,1549]" pageId="9" pageNumber="464">30</emphasis>
Apical portion of metasoma, lateral view
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="A932186EFFD6044CE6ED8C6BDD97326B" blockId="9.[151,1437,1631,2018]" lastBlockId="10.[151,1437,151,1041]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="465" pageId="9" pageNumber="464">
<emphasis id="9BF9C47CFFD6044FE6ED8C6BD94F3550" bold="true" box="[199,325,1632,1658]" pageId="9" pageNumber="464">Mesosoma</emphasis>
. Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="31B604EBFFD6044FE7CA8C6BDA343550" box="[480,574,1632,1658]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–24" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1723,1747]" captionTargetBox="[180,1420,564,1693]" captionTargetId="figure-143@8.[161,1427,561,1700]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 21–24. Megastylus (Megastylus) yindianense Sheng &amp; Li, sp. nov. Holotype. Female. 21 Habitus, lateral view 22 Head, anterior view 23 Head and pronotum, lateral view 24 Head and mesoscutum, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5848343" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5848343/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="464">Figs 23</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="31B604EBFFD6044FE4788C54DA653550" box="[594,623,1631,1658]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1489,1513]" captionTargetBox="[162,1412,282,1456]" captionTargetId="figure-49@9.[162,1424,273,1466]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 25–30. Megastylus (Megastylus) yindianense Sheng &amp; Li, sp. nov. Holotype. Female. 25 Mesosoma, lateral view 26 Propodeum. 27 Front tibia and basal portion of tarsus, lateral view 28 Fore wing 29 Tergites 1–2, lateral view 30 Apical portion of metasoma, lateral view" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5848345" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5848345/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="464">25</figureCitation>
) shiny, anterolateral portion slightly shagreened. Epomia indistinct. Mesoscutum (
<figureCitation id="31B604EBFFD6044FE7168C8FD99F35B4" box="[316,405,1668,1694]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–24" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1723,1747]" captionTargetBox="[180,1420,564,1693]" captionTargetId="figure-143@8.[161,1427,561,1700]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 21–24. Megastylus (Megastylus) yindianense Sheng &amp; Li, sp. nov. Holotype. Female. 21 Habitus, lateral view 22 Head, anterior view 23 Head and pronotum, lateral view 24 Head and mesoscutum, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5848343" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5848343/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="464">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
) strongly convex, shiny, slightly shagreened; notauli weakly vestigial at anterior end. Scutoscutellar groove smooth, shiny. Scutellum (
<figureCitation id="31B604EBFFD6044FE4948CA3DB0835E8" box="[702,770,1704,1730]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1678,1702]" captionTargetBox="[175,1414,454,1653]" captionTargetId="figure-139@3.[173,1414,453,1655]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–9. Megastylus (Dicolus) mentouense Sheng &amp; Li, sp. nov. Holotype. Male. 5 Mesoscutum and scutellum, dorsal view 6 Mesosoma, lateral view 7 Postscutellum, Prepropodeum and propodeum 8 Tergite 1, dorsal view 9 Tergites 2–3, dorsal view" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5848335" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5848335/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="464">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
) convex, with texture as mesoscutum, lateral carina almost reaching posterior end. Postscutellum small, smooth. Mesopleuron (
<figureCitation id="31B604EBFFD6044FE5A98CC7DBD935CC" box="[899,979,1739,1766]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1489,1513]" captionTargetBox="[162,1412,282,1456]" captionTargetId="figure-49@9.[162,1424,273,1466]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 25–30. Megastylus (Megastylus) yindianense Sheng &amp; Li, sp. nov. Holotype. Female. 25 Mesosoma, lateral view 26 Propodeum. 27 Front tibia and basal portion of tarsus, lateral view 28 Fore wing 29 Tergites 1–2, lateral view 30 Apical portion of metasoma, lateral view" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5848345" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5848345/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="464">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
) finely shagreened; lower portion weakly convex, indistinctly finely punctate; upper end of epicnemial carina distance from front edge of mesopleuron, and 0.6 height to subtegular ridge. Metapleuron evenly convex, with dense fine punctures, distance between punctures 0.2–0.8 × diameter of puncture. Fore femur compressed; basal portion of first tarsomere (
<figureCitation id="31B604EBFFD6044FE2AE8D33DCDC3478" box="[1156,1238,1848,1874]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1489,1513]" captionTargetBox="[162,1412,282,1456]" captionTargetId="figure-49@9.[162,1424,273,1466]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 25–30. Megastylus (Megastylus) yindianense Sheng &amp; Li, sp. nov. Holotype. Female. 25 Mesosoma, lateral view 26 Propodeum. 27 Front tibia and basal portion of tarsus, lateral view 28 Fore wing 29 Tergites 1–2, lateral view 30 Apical portion of metasoma, lateral view" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5848345" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5848345/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="464">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
) strongly curved, inside with dense fine setae. Hind femur 6.7 × as long as its maximum width. Hind tibia 9.7 × as long as its maximum width; inner profile of apical end with dense distinct fine setae; longer spur 0.3 × as long as first tarsomere. Hind tarsus as long as hind tibia. Ratio of length of hind tarsomeres from first to fifth: 20.0:9.5:6.6:4.5:8.3. Claw small, simple. Wings (
<figureCitation id="31B604EBFFD6044FE7678DC3D9A834C8" box="[333,418,1992,2018]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1489,1513]" captionTargetBox="[162,1412,282,1456]" captionTargetId="figure-49@9.[162,1424,273,1466]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 25–30. Megastylus (Megastylus) yindianense Sheng &amp; Li, sp. nov. Holotype. Female. 25 Mesosoma, lateral view 26 Propodeum. 27 Front tibia and basal portion of tarsus, lateral view 28 Fore wing 29 Tergites 1–2, lateral view 30 Apical portion of metasoma, lateral view" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5848345" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5848345/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="464">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
) slightly brownish, hyaline. Fore wing with vein 1cu-a interstitial. Areolet absent. Vein 2m-cu with two bullae. Postnervulus intercepted slightly below middle. Posterior half of hind wing vein M+CU distinctly arched, 1-cu 2.3 × as long as cu-a, discoidella unpigmented. Without prepropodeum. Propodeum (
<figureCitation id="31B604EBFFD5044CE3458AB0D8BE33D0" captionStart="FIGURES 25–30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1489,1513]" captionTargetBox="[162,1412,282,1456]" captionTargetId="figure-49@9.[162,1424,273,1466]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 25–30. Megastylus (Megastylus) yindianense Sheng &amp; Li, sp. nov. Holotype. Female. 25 Mesosoma, lateral view 26 Propodeum. 27 Front tibia and basal portion of tarsus, lateral view 28 Fore wing 29 Tergites 1–2, lateral view 30 Apical portion of metasoma, lateral view" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5848345" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5848345/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="465">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
) evenly convex, with dense indistinct punctures, posterior transverse carina closing posterior end of propodeum; anteromedian portion with deep transverse smooth concavity, which approximately 0.2 × as long as propodeum; lateromedian and lateral longitudinal carinae absent; apicomedian portion shiny. Propodeal spiracle small, circular.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A932186EFFD5044CE6ED8B40DD083133" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1041]" pageId="10" pageNumber="465">
<emphasis id="9BF9C47CFFD5044CE6ED8B40D949324F" bold="true" box="[199,323,331,357]" pageId="10" pageNumber="465">Metasoma</emphasis>
. Tergite 1 (
<figureCitation id="31B604EBFFD5044CE7EE8B40DA1F324F" box="[452,533,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1489,1513]" captionTargetBox="[162,1412,282,1456]" captionTargetId="figure-49@9.[162,1424,273,1466]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 25–30. Megastylus (Megastylus) yindianense Sheng &amp; Li, sp. nov. Holotype. Female. 25 Mesosoma, lateral view 26 Propodeum. 27 Front tibia and basal portion of tarsus, lateral view 28 Fore wing 29 Tergites 1–2, lateral view 30 Apical portion of metasoma, lateral view" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5848345" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5848345/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="465">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
) with texture as propodeum; shagreened. 3.1 × as long as apical width, posterior half beyond spiracle slightly widened; latero-median and dorso-lateral carinae absent; ventro-lateral carina complete. spiracle slightly elliptic, located at anterior 0.4 of tergite 1. Tergite 2 strongly widened posteriorly; same longth as posterior width, 0.8 × as long as tergite 1; with almost similar texture to tergite 1. Thyridium elliptic, closed to anterior margin of tergite 2. Third and subsequent tergites shiny, with indistinct fine punctures. Fourth Posterior and subsequent tergites compressed. Ovipositor sheath (
<figureCitation id="31B604EBFFD5044CE4F18BF4DB273133" box="[731,813,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1489,1513]" captionTargetBox="[162,1412,282,1456]" captionTargetId="figure-49@9.[162,1424,273,1466]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 25–30. Megastylus (Megastylus) yindianense Sheng &amp; Li, sp. nov. Holotype. Female. 25 Mesosoma, lateral view 26 Propodeum. 27 Front tibia and basal portion of tarsus, lateral view 28 Fore wing 29 Tergites 1–2, lateral view 30 Apical portion of metasoma, lateral view" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5848345" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5848345/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="465">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
) 0.6 as long as apical depth of metasoma.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A932186EFFD5044CE6ED8829DD0131DB" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1041]" pageId="10" pageNumber="465">
<emphasis id="9BF9C47CFFD5044CE6ED8829D9423116" bold="true" box="[199,328,546,572]" pageId="10" pageNumber="465">Coloration</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="31B604EBFFD5044CE7738828D9A73117" box="[345,429,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–24" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1723,1747]" captionTargetBox="[180,1420,564,1693]" captionTargetId="figure-143@8.[161,1427,561,1700]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 21–24. Megastylus (Megastylus) yindianense Sheng &amp; Li, sp. nov. Holotype. Female. 21 Habitus, lateral view 22 Head, anterior view 23 Head and pronotum, lateral view 24 Head and mesoscutum, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5848343" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5848343/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="465">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
). Black, except for following: Scape, pedicel and basal portion of flagellomeres blackish brown. Setae of flagellomeres almost black. Face black, obscurely slightly reddish. Maxillary palpi and labial palpi yellow. Clypeus, propleuron, lower portion of pronotum, mesopleuron except upper anterior portion darkish brown, mesosternum, hind coxa, hind femur except apex, hind tibia except subbase and apex slightly black, reddish brown. Fore and mid legs and hind trochanter yellowish brown. Hind tarsus brownish black. posterior margin of tergite 2, anterior half of tergite 3 and posterior margin yellowish white. Pterostigma and veins brownish black.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E1974BE5FFD5044CE6ED88F1DA2A303F" box="[199,544,762,789]" pageId="10" pageNumber="465" type="distribution">
